default by crossing type, location,
default amount and type of use,
default 
defaultand other local factors. 
defaultSafety risk can 
defaultsometimes 
defaultbe reduced by 
defaultchanging
default the crossing type 
defaultus
defaulted in a particular location, but doing so 
defaultcan be expensive
default and not 
defaultproportionate to the reduction
default in risk
default achieved. 
defaultIn some locations more modest changes, such as removing obstructions from sight lines, improving the visibility of road traffic signals and 
defaultincreas
defaulting the audibility of train horns,
default 
defaultmay be more appropriate and cost effective. The rail industry, through 
defaultNetwork Rail
default,
default is taking a number of steps to achieve further safety improvements, including:
