defaultThe benefits resulting 
defaultfrom improvements to level crossings are not limited to 
defaultincreased safety and reduced risk. For the railway, improvements can lead to quicker journey times through fewer speed restrictions and lower maintenance and staffing costs (depending on the improvement made). At the same time there are often
default benefits to r
defaultoad users, in the form of reduced delays and a better flow of traffic. Given the benefits of improvements are shared between rail and road and that 
defaultl
defaultevel crossing accidents tend to 
defaultinvolve road users and 
defaultpedestrians rather than rail passengers
default, 
defaultthere 
defaultis 
defaulta 
defaultstrong 
defaultcase for 
defaultusing the
default roads budget 
defaultto supplement the existing commitment from
default 
defaultthe 
defaultrail budget
default to fund further improvements.
